The `toString()`(#e7e8ea) method in the `Object`(#e7e8ea) class returns a `String`(#e7e8ea) that consists of the name of the class, the @ symbol, and the hash code of the object.

The `toString()`(#e7e8ea) method is automatically called when an object reference is passed to a print statement or when an object reference is concatenated with a `String`(#e7e8ea).

We can override the `toString()`(#e7e8ea) method in our classes to provide more useful information about the state of our objects.
```
 public String toString() {
   return topping + " pizza";
}
```
